# Honch Integrator

When asked to add, install, set up, or wire up Honch, follow the procedure in the
installed skill body under `.honch/honch-integrator/`:

1. Read `.honch/honch-integrator/content/integrator.md` (full workflow + the hard
   "no edits before confirmation" gate + the universal trap checklist).
2. Detect the path with `.honch/honch-integrator/content/detection.md`, then read
   the matching `.honch/honch-integrator/content/<path>.md`.
3. Plan → confirm (one explicit go-ahead) → implement → verify the build, then
   walk `.honch/honch-integrator/content/production-checklist.md`.

Non-negotiables: no edits before plan approval; delivery must be pumped
(`tick()`/`flush()`) or events never upload; device ports need ≥ 8192-byte stack
and an NTP-synced clock; identity merges need a `$identify` with
`$anon_distinct_id`; keep the API key out of source control. Targets SDK 0.3.0.
